         <p><hi rend="bold">Easter Monday, April 21</hi><hi rend="bold superscript underline">st</hi><hi rend="bold">, 1924.</hi></p>
         <p>A warm bright morning but with an insecure promise for the day. The chimney in my study smoked constantly, rendering the room almost uninhabitable, a circumstance the more exasperating since I had much to do in preparation for my departure this afternoon. It is ever so: one's instruments break and fail precisely when they are most needed! This is as true of human instruments as of the others, &amp; more trustworthy kind.</p>
